related_items.title: Photographs of news events and people from the papers of journalist Ethel L. Payne
description: 325 photographic prints : chiefly gelatin silver, b&w ; 8 x 10 in. or smaller. | 161 photographic prints : color ; 8 x 10 in. or smaller. | 1 drawing : graphite, b&w ; 19.5 x 12.5 cm. | Photographs show national and international news events, meetings, and people in the news.  Includes Payne and other African American journalists attending press club meetings and a Black Press Seminar in New York City; United Nations meetings; White House ceremonies with Presidents Lyndon Johnson and John F. Kennedy; U.S. Presidents and politicians including, Richard Nixon, Jimmy Carter, Adam Clayton Powell, and Walter Washington.  Also includes color and black-and-white photographs of Payne's 1990 visit with Nelson and Winnie Mandela at their home in Soweto, S.A.; some general views of South Africa; other photographs relating to various news events in Africa, including World Bank activities in Ghana, Kenya, and Nigeria; activities and people of the Namibia South West African Peoples Organisation (SWAPO); Henry Kissinger meeting with leaders in Liberia and Senegal; Payne interviewing Somalian President, Siad Barre; the 1985 United Nations Decade for Women World Conference at Nairobi, Kenya; photographs from the 1975 International Women's Year Tribune in Mexico; snapshots from Payne's 1973 trip to China; images of Chinese workers and students, a few distant views of the Great Wall.  Also formal and informal portraits of Payne (including a press pass); Payne's family and acquaintances; one portrait sketch of a girl (sitter unidentified).
